cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with facial attribute classification using deep learning techniques and wearable cameras. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of contextual information, such as location and weather, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The use of deep learning techniques for feature representation could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper involves the use of wearable cameras, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the use of image pairs and similarity measures, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
